@startuml seq-diff-split-enrich
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because the split view's DISTINGUISHING move is a round trip across the amber IPC
'' seam to read the on-disk pre/post files — a sequence with an activation bar and a seam-crossing pull
'' expresses that far better than a flowchart, and the palette keeps amber = IPC everywhere.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Split diff — enriching the hunk window with the on-disk pre/post files

participant "`[Unified | Split]`\ntoggle" as Toggle APPDB_TINT
participant "renderer\n(diff view)" as Rend RENDERER_TINT
participant "preload seam\n`window.vv`" as Seam IPC_TINT
participant "main.service" as Main MAIN_TINT
participant "disk\n(pre / post files)" as FS FS_TINT

== unified (no round trip) ==
Toggle -> Rend : select Unified
note right of Rend #D8F0E6: unified renders from the `.diff` ALONE —\nhunks + `data-*` gutters, no filesystem read

== switch to split ==
Toggle -> Rend : select Split
Rend -> Seam : `vv:load-diff-sources`\n{old-path, new-path}
activate Seam
Seam -> Main : ipc invoke
activate Main
Main -> FS : read old + new files\n(full context beyond the hunk window)
FS --> Main : old-text, new-text
Main --> Seam : {old, new}
deactivate Main
Seam --> Rend : {old, new}
deactivate Seam
Rend -> Rend : align hunks over the full files\n-> old | new columns
note over Rend #FFF6D6: the terminal (vv-cli/tui) has NO split view —\nit renders the unified ANSI diff only

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| view toggle (app-db) |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| renderer diff view |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| IPC seam |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| main.service |
  |<#9F8766>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| on-disk pre/post files |
  Unified is self-contained; split enriches with the files on disk.
endlegend
@enduml
